## GitHub Action Rules

- Check if `package.json` exists in project root and summarize key scripts
- Check if `.nvmrc` exists in project root
- Check if `.env.example` exists in project root to identify key `env:` variables
- Always use `git branch -a | cat` to verify whether we use `main` or `master` branch
- Always use `env:` variables and secrets attached to jobs instead of global workflows
- Always use `npm ci` for Node-based dependency setup
- Extract common steps into composite actions in separate files when they grow
- When adding public actions, verify latest major version (e.g. `actions/checkout@v4`, `actions/setup-node@v4`)
- If linter complains about action parameters, fetch `action.yml` from the action repo to confirm schema
